<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>South Poyang Basin | Guangping Zeng</title><link>https://gpingz.github.io/tags/south-poyang-basin/</link><atom:link href="https://gpingz.github.io/tags/south-poyang-basin/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>South Poyang Basin</description><generator>HugoBlox Kit (https://hugoblox.com)</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 01 Jan 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://gpingz.github.io/media/icon_hu_eee4a95885829ab2.png</url><title>South Poyang Basin</title><link>https://gpingz.github.io/tags/south-poyang-basin/</link></image><item><title>Paleogeographic environment characteristics of the Guanshan Member of the Leping Formation in the Erjiacun Depression, southern Poyang Basin</title><link>https://gpingz.github.io/publications/south-poyang-basin/</link><pubDate>Sat, 01 Jan 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gpingz.github.io/publications/south-poyang-basin/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Fault-Block Oil &amp;amp; Gas Field, 29(2), 199-206. Published in Chinese.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>South Poyang Basin: Paleoenvironment and Organic Matter Enrichment</title><link>https://gpingz.github.io/projects/south-poyang-basin/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Jan 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gpingz.github.io/projects/south-poyang-basin/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This project uses sequence stratigraphy and geochemical records to reconstruct
depositional environments in the South Poyang Basin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work links paleogeography, water-depth and sediment-supply changes, and
organic matter enrichment. It represents the surface-environment and resource
side of my broader interest in Earth material cycles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Poyang fieldwork was a mix of outcrops, cores, sampling teamwork, and
some very improvised logistics.&lt;/p&gt;
